---
title: Vault IAM Auth - Data Flow
---
sequenceDiagram
    box rgb(232,245,253) EC2 Instance Trust Boundary
        participant TF as Terraform Plan
        participant EXT as External Data Source<br/>(aws/vault-iam-auth.sh)
        participant IMDS as EC2 IMDS<br/>(169.254.169.254)
    end

    box rgb(255,253,231) Vault Trust Boundary
        participant VP as Vault Provider
        participant VAUTH as Vault Auth<br/>(/v1/auth/aws/login)
        participant VSE as Vault Secrets Engine<br/>(/v1/aws/creds/:role or /v1/aws/sts/:role)
    end

    box rgb(252,228,236) AWS Trust Boundary
        participant STS as AWS STS
        participant TGTAWS as Target AWS Services
    end

    Note over TF,TGTAWS: Authentication Phase (external data source execution)
    TF->>EXT: Execute program
    EXT->>IMDS: GET /2020-10-27/meta-data/iam/info
    IMDS-->>EXT: InstanceProfileArn
    EXT->>IMDS: GET /2020-10-27/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/{profile}
    IMDS-->>EXT: AccessKeyId, SecretAccessKey, Token
    Note over EXT: AWS Signature v4:<br/>1. CanonicalRequest = POST / signed headers body<br/>(includes X-Vault-AWS-IAM-Server-Id header)<br/>2. StringToSign = algo + date + scope + hash(canonical)<br/>3. SigningKey = HMAC(HMAC(HMAC(HMAC(AWS4+secret,date),region),sts),aws4_request)<br/>4. Signature = hex(HMAC(SigningKey, StringToSign))
    EXT-->>TF: JSON {role, iam_http_request_method,<br/>iam_request_url (b64), iam_request_body (b64),<br/>iam_request_headers (b64)}

    Note over TF,TGTAWS: Vault Login Phase (provider initialization)
    TF->>VP: Configure with signed payload
    VP->>VAUTH: POST /v1/auth/aws/login<br/>{role, iam_http_request_method,<br/>iam_request_url (b64), iam_request_body (b64),<br/>iam_request_headers (b64)}
    VAUTH->>STS: Replay signed request:<br/>POST sts.amazonaws.com<br/>Action=GetCallerIdentity&Version=2011-06-15
    STS-->>VAUTH: 200 OK (Account, Arn, UserId)
    VAUTH-->>VP: client_token,<br/>policies, ttl

    Note over TF,TGTAWS: Credential Issuance Phase (ephemeral resource)
    VP->>VSE: GET /v1/aws/creds/:role or /v1/aws/sts/:role<br/>(X-Vault-Token: [vault_token])
    Note over VSE: Vault uses its own stored<br/>AWS credentials to call STS
    VSE->>STS: AssumeRole or GetFederationToken
    STS-->>VSE: Temporary credentials:<br/>AccessKeyId (ASIA...),<br/>SecretAccessKey, SessionToken,<br/>Expiration
    VSE-->>VP: access_key, secret_key,<br/>security_token, lease_id, lease_duration

    Note over TF,TGTAWS: Resource Management Phase (plan/apply)
    VP->>TF: Configure AWS provider with JIT creds
    TF->>TGTAWS: API calls to AWS services<br/>(EC2, S3, IAM, etc.)
    Note over TGTAWS: Credentials auto-expire<br/>after lease_duration
